description: This is a randomly ordered feed of the most recent entries from INsmh, skipping any feeds with errors.

items.title: The Great Tech Irony: Build the AI, Then Get Replaced by It
items.description: So Advanced, It Doesn’t Need You Anymore. Turns out that diploma and four years of ramen noodles might just earn you…unemployment. While everyone’s pointing fingers at Trump’s tariffs for a sluggish job market, the real culprit slipping under the radar is A.I. Entry-level tech gigs are vanishing faster than a college grad’s optimism, as companies replace fresh faces with lines of code and chatbot interns. The unemployment rate for recent grads (22-27) is now worse than it is for everyone else in the general workforce. Because nothing says “bright future” like competing with an algorithm. SMH. Read for yourself.

items.title: Camping Out Two Months for a Toy?
items.description: From Tokyo to Times Square, grown men in Mario hats and midnight mobs outside Best Buy prove once again that nothing gets humanity moving like a new plastic box with blinking lights. Nintendo’s Switch 2 hit shelves at the stroke of midnight, prompting global fanfare, musical performances, and cosplay that would make your uncle roll his eyes so hard he’d sprain something. The scenes? Lines wrapped around buildings, celebratory whoops, and thirtysomethings crying tears of joy over the chance to drop $400 on a handheld device that’s already behind in graphics. SMH.
